By IGE ADEKUNLESANGO-OTA (OGUN)- The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Ogun Command, has warned commercial motorcyclists to desist from taking laws into their hands whenever a crisis occurs involving their fellow riders.The Sector Commander of FRSC, Mr Ahmed Umar, gave the warning in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Friday in Ota, Ogun.Umar said the warning became necessary as it had been observed that the commercial motorcyclists, popularly known as Okada riders, usually take laws into their hands whenever crisis erupted between them and the public.“The law enforcement agencies, especially the police, should be allowed to do their duty by enforcing laws so as to ensure sanity whenever such crisis arises,” he said.The Sector Commander enjoined commercial motorcyclists to be cautious on the highways, and adhere strictly to traffic rules and regulations to reduce crashes.He advised them to always use their helmets to avoid hitting their heads on the roads whenever there is a crash. (NAN) By MOHAMMED TIJJANI •The 50 newly promoted officers of the FRSC Kaduna Sector Command Kaduna- The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Kaduna Sector Command, on Friday, decorated 50 newly promoted officers with their new ranks.Addressing the officers in Kaduna, the FRSC Sector Commander, Mr Hafiz Mohammed, urged the newly promoted… In "Metro" •Murdered sound engineer, David LAGOS - Operatives of the Lagos State Police Command have arrested four suspects over the killing of a young man by commercial motorcyclists in the Lekki area of Lagos State. It was gathered that the father of two was killed over N100 balance by the motorcyclists.… In "Metro" By IBIRONKE ARIYO L-R . Osita Chidoka, former Corps Marshal, FRSC, Boboye Oyeyemi, Corps Marshal, FRSC, Goodluck Jonathan, former President of Nigeria and Bisi Kazeem, Corps Public Education Officer, FRSC when the former President came to renew his driver’s licence in FRSC Headquarters, Abuja today ABUJA- Former President Goo